<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
The pattern @Vyou{{}}@HI{{tosuru}} is used to mean "try to do something" or "just as I was about to do something".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{child}}ha@KJ{{one^life}}kenmei@KJ{{hand}}wo@KJ{{expand}}bashite,@KT{{te-buru}}no@KJ{{above}}no
      omochawo@KJ{{take}}routoshiteiru.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The child reaches out and tries as hard as he can to take the toy that is on the table.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
The pattern @Vyou{{}}@HI{{tosuru}} can also mean "just as I was about to do something".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{house}}wo@KJ{{exit}}youtoshitatoki,@KJ{{stab^sort*of*thing^large^rain}}ga@KJ{{descend}}ri@KJ{{exit}}shita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Just as I was about to go out, it started to rain.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

